<br>
1)  Mage's have the hardest time getting groups, few people aside from other mage's know how powerful we are.  Our pets have several K hp and hit in the 50's, our nukes aren't as good as Wizards but can come fairly close, and we get the best AE spells aside from Druids, maybe.  Groups don't know this so if you see people shouting for group members send tells asap trying to get in cause you can spend an hour and a half sometimes shouting for a group and never get one<br>
<br>
2)  Grouping rules:  Always keep control over your pet, one of the worst things that can happen to a group, and one of the main reasons people don't want mage's is because their afriad we wont be able to control our pet and he will start breaking mez or attacking the wrong mob or something.  Don't send you pet in until the warrior has agro and remember to USE YOUR ASSIT KEY!  warriors get very angry when they have to keep bailing the mage out of trouble cause their pet wont stop attacking the wrong mob.  Remember your pets agro is the same thing as your agro so when you cast your adding to the agro and its easy for the mob to want to attack you.  <br>
<br>
3)  If you can't get a group, go soloing, there are plenty of spots to solo at.  BW, DL, KC entrance (just be careful of trains), and other such spots.  just watch your pets hp and the enemy mobs, if the mob seems to be doing better than the pet nuke once or twice then sit back down; away from the mob cause you wil have some majorly bad agro for a few moments.  Also its best to use the air pet if your soloing,  It has lots of agi and will take less dmg, its stun spell is very useful too.  Earth has most hp but no agi and will take max dmg from hits almost every time.  and use your Dmg shield!  It can really add up in a fight!  If your soloing you should also use your bolt nukes since they have great range, and have a SoW potion or two on hand, unless you have Jboots; just incase something goes wrong.  <br>
<br>
4)  The fastest exp, if you want to know, is with one a druid or bard; perhaps enchanter, as a partner.  That way your pet wont take half the exp and you get max exp from group.  I teamed up with Isay in BW and got mad exp from it.  When soloing against the same mobs I got less cause of the exp my pet took.  Mage's are probably one of the best soloing partners in EQ, mainly because you have a tank/nuker/AEer/manamachine with several other things rolled into one class.  If we had fear and snare we'd be unbeatable!  Its best to stay in places where you have a place to run if something goes wrong, places like BW and DL where you have several zones close by are the best, then if something goes wrong you can have a place to run too, I don't suggest dungeons since its so easy to get adds which you might not be prepared to deal with.  <br>
<br>
5)  Use your buffs to best effect, the armor bufs add a very nice regen for hp, and a minimal mana effect, it can mean a lot when your injured and running around trying to get away from a mob to get your hp back faster.  Also use your Hp buffs, they can save your life, I know they've saved mine!<br>
<br>
6)  Watch your mana as much as possible, cause if you pull something while soloing and are lom your probably dead unless the mob is weak, and never make the mistake of under estimating your enemy, they can surprise you!<br>
<br>
I hope this helps you somewhat, and if your can do as I can and make your pet jump through hoops your a good mage!  Hope you guys can add something to this and make it an even better Post<br>
<br>
