<br>
some points that Every class should know....<br>
<br>
1) Every class has their levels in which they are not the most useful to a group...for some classes however the level range is small and perhaps low level...for instance, at low level 12 or so a druid or shaman can be as effective as a cleric, in some cases a shaman is prefered since it has sow at level 9.  Mages fall into this range for awhile, level 29 to 50+ however, this is when their soloing might comes to its true power (if done right).  At level 50 i soloed a 100 percent MR level 50 guard in the karana's, soloed ice giants down going to vox's priest, and almost had the PoD.<br>
<br>
2)  The main reason for mages getting a bad rap, and i'm sure people will hate me for this, i've seen really good mages and i've seen really crappy mages....not implying anything about the people in this guild...i've just never seen a so/so mage.<br>
<br>
Tips to being The Mage:<br>
<br>
1) Know your spell book, no matter how you organize it, know what spells are in what slot....this is easy for the most used spells, but sometimes its the least used spells that are needed FAST.<br>
<br>
2)  Know your pets, sit down and calculate the average damage and hp of each pet, as well as the rate at which they are hit...sometimes earth pet is not the prefered on low mana.<br>
<br>
3)  Wizards out nuke us...but in the long run a mage can do more damage than a wizard any day of the week....wizards will argue, but i've fought a fight for 10 minutes and ended with 20 percent mana.  I'll let you figure that out =o)  BTW this was at level 50 and i had crappy gear =o)<br>
<br>
4)  Don't get hung up on Necro's do this, Druids do this, Wizard do this...where do mages fit in?  Bend the rules...make due with that you have.  Sounds hard, but the mages, if played well, are a VERY prefered class.<br>
<br>
5)  Enchanters won't fear you if your good....Ask any enchanter what is their worst fear....10 to 1 they say a pet, or a newbie who's bought a level 60 melee.  You CAN use your pet both to play crowd control, AND you CAN pull a pet consistantly off of a mes....cuspid has seen me do this in hate against a mob that wasn't slowed...consistantly....practice this, if you can do this mages you are the prefered damage dealing caster hands down.<br>
<br>
Other tips:<br>
<br>
Get those HP up!  not sure what going rate for level 55 mage hp are, but syden had near 1700hp self buffed....i could literally nuke hard, stand in there to get mobs off cleric, or enchanter, have my pet on it and live.<br>
<br>
Mod rods...a chanter gets low on mana, startmodulating them...common sense i know, but VERY few people ever do this in the middle of a fight....you can nuke your heart out, but if the cleric or enchanter dies you fooked...save some mana for mod rods 25 percent is what i used to use as my soft cap.<br>
<br>
Train the pet!<br>
<br>
This is where you become the most valuable...Cleric oom, enchanter oom, tanks and melee 25 percent health...one mob full hp...you can literally take care of it for 10 minutes as long as its one mob...2 mages you can prolly take care of 4mobs at a time.  (My record with Ropise is 14 mob train in KC taken out by 2 mages...no healers).  <br>
<br>
Cast pet, send pet in.<br>
<br>
watch pet's health, monitor rate it is going down<br>
start casting pet (10 seconds or so-seems like forever)<br>
hit enter<br>
type in:  /pet get lost<br>
wait til you are half a bub of casting time left<br>
hit enter<br>
use hot key to send new pet in on old target (prefered to use earth pet for this in most cases)<br>
<br>
<br>
if you have 2 or 3 mages doing this, its a joke, you can literally med 95 percent of the casting cost for that pet back by the time you need to summon another one...at 5 percent mana loss per pet you are looking at 20 pets by the time you have to book that zone, thats also dependent on if you have a mod rod somewhere on you before the fight.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'm sure most of you guys knew this, but for some non mage players, this might open the world of tactics up for the guild...considering the amount of mages we have in the guild now...level 60 mob will summon if a mage sits down too long, however standing up chances are it will leave you alone...great way to start a figth too...send the pets in mages stand, let the mob get his HT's and dots down, waste his mana on the pets, send in MT (clerics now still have full mana) tank goes in and the pets and mages are now above agro range than the cleric who needs to heal him....its VERY risky for mages and havn't played like this for Luclin...but it works in Kunark for sure.<br>
